article.headline: Pennsylvania 84, The Citadel 49
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- The University of Pennsylvania had a season-high 12 3-pointers in a 84-49 victory over The Citadel Wednesday night. Eric Osmundson led Penn (6-4) with 16 points, including four 3-pointers. Four other players also scored in double digits for Penn. J'mel Everhart captured his fourth double-double of the season for The Citadel (6-7), scoring 14 points and 10 rebounds. Demetrius Nelson, who fouled out with 2:36 remaining, led the Bulldogs with 15 points. The Bulldogs were without freshman Vytautus Valiulis who broke his hand during Christmas break and junior guard Mark Schiavoni who suffered an ankle sprain. Penn led by as many as 37 points on 52 percent shooting. Ibrahim Jaaber contributed 15 points and 3 assists, and David Whitehurst added 14 points including three 3-pointers for the Quakers.
